  "prompt": "Good libraries in old Rajendra Nagar?",
  "response": "Old Rajendra Nagar in Delhi is known for its numerous coaching centers and libraries, primarily catering to students preparing for competitive exams like the Civil Services Examination. Some of the reputed libraries in the area include:\n\n1. **SRCC Library:** Known for its quiet environment and extensive collection of books, particularly useful for those preparing for competitive exams.\n2. **Jawahar Book Depot Library:** Offers a good collection of study material and books related to various competitive exams.\n3. **Rajendra Library:** Popular among students for its comfortable seating and conducive study environment.\n4. **Vision IAS Library:** Associated with the Vision IAS coaching institute, it provides a good space for self-study.\n5. **Chanakya IAS Library:** A well-organized library offering a variety of materials for IAS aspirants.\n6. **Drishti IAS Library:** Another well-known library focusing on providing resources for UPSC candidates.\n7. **Vajiram and Ravi Library:** Linked with the renowned coaching institute, it offers an excellent environment for studying.\n8. **Elite IAS Library:** Known for its peaceful atmosphere and ample resources for aspirants.\n9. **Shubhra Ranjan IAS Study Circle Library:** Offers study materials and a conducive setup for preparation.\n\nThese libraries often have flexible timings and membership options tailored to the needs of students. It\u2019s always a good idea to visit and evaluate a library based on your specific requirements and preferences.",
